parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to malfunction, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle breaks or cracks
the seat belt comes out of the vehicle
the seat belt will not latch
the seat belt buckle releases unexpectedly
the seat belt is unable to be used due to buckle failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the vehicle experiences difficulty starting
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the fuel pump fails to prime
the fuel pump is inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The fuel gauge constantly reads empty
the fuel gauge registers empty when the tank is full
the fuel gauge is inaccurate
the fuel gauge is stuck on empty
the fuel gauge is inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Short in the Alarm System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short in the alarm system can cause a fire, which can lead to vehicle damage, injury, or even death.
symptoms: The alarm system malfunctions
the vehicle catches fire
smoke or flames emerge from the dashboard or electrical components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tilt Steering Column Pivot Pinion Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loosening of the tilt steering column pivot pinion due to vibration can cause the steering wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or locks up
the steering column makes unusual noises or vibrates
the pivot pinion is loose or backed out.
